
To describe three commercial weight loss programs (Jenny Craig, LA Weight Loss, and Weight Watchers), including efficacy data when available, and to provide clinicians with information for patient counseling.

Personal interviews, journal articles, and Web site information.

Commercial weight loss programs provide weight loss services. Benefits are experience, planned menus, and psychological support. Limitations are cost, sales promotions that encourage on-the-spot commitment to prepaid contracts, and the cost of program food and additional vitamins.

Weight loss is a necessary goal for many patients. Clinicians are mandated to provide counseling regarding weight loss.

